profile_positions.description:
Job Opening:
•	Managed day-to-day operation & interface between tenants and owners;
•	Prepared and presented properties quarterly reports to owners;
•	Identified and negotiated with new and current suppliers;
•	Created and developed marketing and communication for shopping malls;
•	Managed promotional budget;
•	Led and coordinated the main food court’s renovations (Carrefour Industrielle Alliance, 800 seats);
•	Researched, planned and executed all major promotional events for shopping malls;
•	Created and managed both company websites from Domain name to layout and content (ahern.ca, carrefourindustriellealliance.com);
•	Prepared Market studies and property analysis for New Customers.

•	Organized and coordinated Tour Groups in the U.S.;
•	Created and prepared itineraries, quotes and proposals for European Tour Operators;
•	Negotiated programs and group rates with U.S. suppliers (hotels, restaurants, entertainment company, attractions sites…); 
•	Realized Pro-active outbound calls for European market.

Job Opening:
•	Organized and coordinated sourcing actions for Group Branches (CIB, AMS, IRS …) in France and Europe; 
•	Managed a team of 3 persons;
•	Main contact for all BNP Paribas branches and schools on sourcing topics;
•	Elaborated and monitored budget for each Education Program (Universities, Colleges);
•	Researched, planned and executed all major recruiting events (workshops, parties and associations events);
•	Coordinated with business lines on effective sell processes;
•	Selected and interviewed candidates for Sales positions;
•	Trained new recruiters and business managers on sourcing actions;
•	Created communications tools for external and internal recruitment (stand, HR film, leaflet, goodies…);
•	Identified and negotiated with new and current suppliers for all events needs.

Job Opening: 
Sales Department animation on youth products 0-25 years:
•	Created and reported on sales actions (sales target);
•	Contributed to corporate marketing strategies through targeted researches and new business development opportunities;
•	Created and organized “youth” communication;
•	Trained account managers on new youth products.
Development of the youth market in several Parisian districts:
•	Main contact for Education Program management and associations;
•	Created partnerships and Relayed national actions;
•	Developed Regional recruiting actions with Retail Banking HR department (conferences, forums…);
•	Coordinated and executed promotions, events and ensured business lines participation.

